[According to the data on the Worldometer website, the total number of cases of COVID-19 worldwide is now 182 605, with 80 881 cases reported by China. There are now a total of 101 724 confirmed cases of COVID-19 reported from 162 countries/locations outside mainland China representing an increase of 12 979 cases when compared with the data on 15 Mar 2020, with Italy accounting for 3233 of the newly reported cases, Iran for 1053 of newly reported cases, and South Korea for 84 of the newly reported cases. Spain (2097), Germany (1459), and France (1210) are major contributors to this increase as well. The total number of confirmed cases reported from outside of China now represents 55.7% of the total number of reported cases. The epicenter has shifted outside of China to Western Europe. There were 18 other countries with more than 30 newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours. A global total of 7171 deaths have been reported, 3945 outside mainland China.

For the 19th consecutive day, more cases have been reported from outside mainland China than within mainland China. And for the 3nd day, the number of newly confirmed cases from South Korea was less than 100. - Mod.MPP]

