[2] China: National Health Commission 16 Mar 2020
Date: Mon 16 Mar 2020
Source: China National Health Commission [in Chinese, machine trans., edited]
http://www.nhc.gov.cn/xcs/yqtb/202003/28d026a0422844969226913ee3d56d77.shtml


At 04:00 on [16 Mar 2020], 31 provinces (autonomous regions, municipalities) and the Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps reported 21 new confirmed cases, 13 new deaths (12 in Hubei, and 1 in Shaanxi), and new suspected cases. 45 cases.

On the same day, 930 new cases were cured and discharged, 1105 close contacts were released from medical observation, and 202 severe cases were improved.

As of 24:00 on [16 Mar 2020], according to reports from 31 provinces (autonomous regions and municipalities) and the Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps, there were 8976 confirmed cases (among which, 2830 were severe cases), 68 869 cases were cured and discharged, and 3226 cases were fatal. A total of 80 881 confirmed cases have been reported and 128 suspected cases have been reported. A total of 681 404 close contacts were tracked, and 9351 were close contacts still in medical observation.

1 newly confirmed case in Hubei (1 in Wuhan), 893 newly cured cases (836 in Wuhan), 12 new deaths (11 in Wuhan), 8701 confirmed cases (8304 in Wuhan), Among them, there were 2782 severe cases (2695 in Wuhan). A total of 55 987 discharged patients were cured (39 220 in Wuhan), 3111 deaths (2480 in Wuhan), and 67 799 confirmed cases (in Wuhan, 4504). There were 0 new suspected cases (0 in Wuhan) and 3 existing suspected cases (1 in Wuhan).

At 04:00 on [16 Mar 2020], 20 newly diagnosed imported cases were reported (9 in Beijing, 3 in Shanghai, 3 in Guangdong, 1 in Zhejiang, 1 in Shandong, 1 in Guangxi, 1 in Yunnan, and 1 in Shaanxi). As of 24:00 on [16 Mar 2020], a total of 143 confirmed imported cases were reported overseas.

A total of 235 confirmed cases were reported from Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan: 157 cases in Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (88 cases discharged, 4 deaths), 11 cases in Macau Special Administrative Region (10 cases discharged), 67 cases in Taiwan (22 cases discharged, 1 case died).

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
and
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Kunihiko Iizuka

[According to the report above, a total of 80 881 cases of confirmed COVID-19 have now been reported from China, representing an increase of 21 cases in the past 24 hours since yesterday's (15 Mar 2020) report was prepared.

It is now the 8th consecutive day that the number of newly reported cases in a 24 hour period was less than 50. While there are still suspected cases reported that presumably are waiting for laboratory confirmation, fingers are crossed this adequately represents China approaching interruption of the SARS-CoV-2 transmission in the country. In addition, 13 deaths were reported, all of them by Hubei province. Nine new cases were reported from Hong Kong.

There were 20 imported cases into China confirmed, representing 95.2% of all reported cases in the past 24 hours. Hence, all but 1 of the newly confirmed cases were imported cases - approaching interruption of transmission! Cases were reported by Beijing (9), Shanghai (3), Guangdong (3) Zhejiang (1), Shandong (1), Guangxi (1) Yunnan (1), and Shaanxi (1), bringing the total number of imported cases to 143. As I keep mentioning, a challenge will be to prevent importations from starting new chains of transmission within China. The 1 remaining case with local transmission, was from Wuhan in Hubei province. Interpretation: Wuhan is the location within China where the SARS-CoV-2 is still being transmitted. Albeit it appears to be approaching interruption of transmission. I remain interested in seeing a table of locations of origin of imported cases.

A map of China showing provinces can be seen at https://www.chinadiscovery.com/china-maps/china-provincial-map.html and a HealthMap/ProMED-mail map is available at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7101282,155. - Mod.MPP]

