[Note that the reporting interval is now midnight to midnight, presenting the full calendar day. In the past 24 hours, the tally of confirmed cases of COVID-19 in South Korea has increased by 84 cases and 6 deaths as compared with yesterday's 24 hour period (15-16 Mar 2020) when there were 74 newly confirmed cases. The epicenter of this outbreak is still Daegu province with 6098 reported cases and the surrounding province of Gyeongbuk with 1169 reported cases. That being said, there is still significant activity seen in Seoul (12 new cases) and Gyeonggi (31 new cases). Daily case counts are slowing down with only 5 newly confirmed cases in Gyeongbuk in the past 24 hours, and only 32 cases reported from Daegu. There were 11 provinces not reporting any new cases. Interestingly there are now 6 individuals in quarantine (up from 4 the day before), detected through airport screening, who have tested positive.

A map of South Korea showing provinces can be seen at https://www.nationsonline.org/oneworld/map/korea-south-administrative-map.htm and a HealthMap/ProMED-mail map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7101282,195. - Mod.MPP]

